race.comment: VERY TORQUEE (8) has placed in all three runs to date, narrowly beaten into second at Wodonga, going down by a long neck. This looks like a very winnable maiden post-scratchings with a handful of dangers coming out. Going the right way and can break through. BLUE TYPHOON (10) ran a much better race last start at Ararat when beaten under a length into third. She was fresh for that run and can improve now. PARISH PRIEST (18) resumes for his second campaign. It's worth noting he started $2.40 favourite on debut at Cranbourne and ran well before struggling at Geelong and being tipped out. The pieces are there to say he has the ability to take this out, keep safe. OPULENT OSCAR (5) is a Hanseatic gelding on debut who has jumped out well and has claims.
